sql:
SELECT DISTINCT user_id
FROM access_logs
WHERE location_id = (SELECT id FROM locations WHERE name = 'Specific Location');

SELECT severity, COUNT(id) AS alert_count
FROM weather_alerts
GROUP BY severity;

external_knowledge:
- Beacon lights up brightest: Metaphor for the location with the highest temperature;
- American sky: Refers to locations within the United States;
- When it shines: Refers to the date and time when the highest temperature was recorded;
- Surroundings: Refers to the location name and country;
- Lowest temperature it encountered during that glow: Refers to the lowest temperature (templow) recorded alongside the highest temperature.
